    <div id="content">
        <h1>Introduction</h1>
        <p>This report collected over than 22,000 homicides which were got from FBI's Supplementary Homicide Report and 
		Freedom of Information Act from 1980 to 2014. The dataset I used for this report can be found at <a href="https://www.kaggle.com/murderaccountability/homicide-reports/downloads/homicide-reports.zip/1">Kaggle</a>
		, and it was compiled and made available by the Murder Accountability Project, founded by Thomas Hargrove. </br>
		&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp In the following analysis, we will be looking for the distribution of the homicide incidents in the USA, the 
		sex/race/age of the perpetrator and the victim and also looking for the most used weapon.
		</p>
		</br>
	
	<br /><br /><br />
	
	<!--D3-->
	<div class="graph">
	<div class="image_description">The Homicide incident count from 1980 to 2014</div>
	<div id="year"
			style="width:650px; height:450px;"></div>
			
	<p>From this line chart, we can see the homicide incident <span class='highlight_color_red'>decreased</span> from <span class='highlight_color_pink'>1991</span> and touched the bottom in 2000, 
	but after that, it <span class='highlight_color_red'>increased rapidly</span> again from <span class='highlight_color_pink'>2001</span> ,and reached the highest then did not down much till <span class='highlight_color_pink'>2014</span> . </p>
			
	<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />
	
			
